column4: UPDATE 4-Apple's 9-year iPhone juggernaut stops with first sales decline
column5: April 26 Apple Inc on Tuesday posted its first-ever decline in iPhone sales and its first revenue drop in 13 years as the company credited with inventing the smartphone struggles with an increasingly saturated market.
